    * LOTS of bugfixes
    * LOTS of improvements


pysocket 0.1.5 (2015-03-21)
===========================
After this release, testing will start. Here's what's changed:

    * All of the send functions for the socket
    * All of the socket functions except for socket.shutdown, which is replaced by socket.unbind
    * Cleared up some code
    * Fixed typos


pysocket 0.1.0 (2015-03-19)
===========================
This release adds more functions to pysocket. Here's what's new:

    * All of the recv functions for the socket
    * A send function which is a better version of the socket.send


pysocket 0.0.7 (2015-03-16)
===========================
Here's what's new in v0.0.7:

    * More functions in the socket class
    * Code is now formated
    * Better exception handling


pysocket 0.0.3 (2015-03-12)
===========================
This is the first release of pysocket, which is currently in version 0.0.3. Here's what is currently implemented:

    * A socket class (replaces socket.socket), in which currently implemented is:
        * Most of the socket.socket functions
        * Some additional functions (most are to control how the socket works)
        * Better error messages for some socket errors
        * Socket doesn't raise error on timeout
